com.amazon.insights
Interface InsightsHandler<T>

public interface InsightsHandler<T>

InsightsHandler is a handle to any asynchronous long-running operation, such as ABTestClient.getVariations(String...), which allows you to assign a callback that is notified on completion (whether successful or not) of the operation.

Method Summary
 void setCallback(InsightsCallback<T> callback)
          This method provides access to the return object of the async call via a callback object.
 

Method Detail

setCallback

void setCallback(InsightsCallback<T> callback)

This method provides access to the return object of the async call via a callback object. Once the async call completes, it will invoke the callback if it is already set. If the callback is not set, and the async call completes, it will invoke the callback immediately when set. Note that setCallback only registers the first callback set to this handler; any subsequent assignments will be ignored.

An example of how to set a callback into the handler:

 // Get a handler somewhere
 InsightsHandler<VariationSet> handler = ...;
 
 // Set a callback for the handler to use
 handler.setCallback(new InsightsCallback<VariationSet>() {
     public void onComplete(VariationSet result) {
         // use result
     }
     
     // optional onError(InsightsError error) implementation
 });

Parameters:
callback - the InsightsCallback<T> object
